{"lemma":"أُسْرَةٌ","slug":"أُسْرَةٌ","root":"#.س.ر","root_slug":"_-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n742","n750","n19413"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"family"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سَرِير (sarīr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔus.ra/","/ʔa.sir.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n742","headword_ar":"اَسَرَهُ","root":"Asr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asorN","text_ar":"اَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaArN","text_ar":"اـِسَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound, braced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely, his captive,] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,) namely, his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or camel's saddle], (S, A,) or his horse's saddle, (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaAr","text_ar":"اـِسَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thong of untanned hide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by tying the two extremities of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroquwotaAni","text_ar":"عَرْقُوْتَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camel's saddle, or of the curved pieces of wood of the horse's saddle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  Also, aor. as above, and so the inf. n., i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asorN","text_ar":"اَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaArN","text_ar":"اـِسَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him a captive; captived him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took him a prisoner; whether he bound him with an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaAr","text_ar":"اـِسَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=srhu","text_ar":"ا=سرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the same form as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akorama","text_ar":"اَكْرَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstA^srhu","text_ar":"استاسرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to a trad., in which it occurs thus used, transitively: (Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he imprisoned him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) ―         -b3-  Also, (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asorN","text_ar":"اَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a goodly manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asarahu A@ll~`hu A^aHosana AlA^asori","text_ar":"اَسَرَهُ ا@للّٰهُ اَحْسَنَ الاَسْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God created him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formed him, in the best manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usira","text_ar":"اُسِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuw^osaru","text_ar":"يُوْسَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asira","text_ar":"اَسِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^osaru","text_ar":"يَاْسَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IKtt;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usira bawoluhu","text_ar":"اُسِرَ بَوْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asorN","text_ar":"اَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, and so in a copy of the S,) or the latter is a simple subst.; (M, IKtt;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffered suppression of his urine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, IKtt, A.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usorN","text_ar":"اُسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","K","TA","Msb","Lth","Mgh","God"]},{"entry_id":"n750","headword_ar":"اُسْرَةٌ","root":"Asr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsmen that are more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, nearly related to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near kinsmen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, A, * Msb, * K:) or a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearest, relations on his father's side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Jaafar En-Nahhás:) so called because he is strengthened by them. (S, A.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19413","headword_ar":"اسرّهُ","root":"sr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isoraArN","text_ar":"اـِسْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) [and accord. to the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sar~ahu","text_ar":"سَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but see the first sentence of this art.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He concealed it; suppressed it; kept it secret;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) namely, a story, or the like: (A, Mgh, Msb:) and, contr.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he manifested it; revealed it; published it; made it known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K.) Both of these significations have been assigned to the verb in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^asar~uwA A@ln~adaAmapa","text_ar":"وَاَسَرُّوا ا@لنَّدَامَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [x. 55 and xxxiv. 32]: (S:) some say, that the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They will manifest repentance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Th says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they will conceal it"},{"kind":"text","text":"from their chiefs: the former [says ISd] is the more correct: (M:) the former meaning is also given on the authority of AO; but Sh says, I have not heard it on the authority of any other; and Az says that the lexicologists most strongly disapprove of the saying of AO; and it is said that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the chiefs of the polytheists,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will conceal repentance"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the lower class of their people, whom they shall have caused to err; and in like manner say Zj and the [other] expositors. (TA.) In like manner also the two contr. significations are assigned to the verb in the saying of Imra-el- Keys, [in his Mo'allakah,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo yusir~uwna maqotaliY","text_ar":"لَوْ يُسِرُّونَ مَقْتَلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which As used to quote with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo yu$ir~uwna","text_ar":"لَوْ يُشِرُّونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqotaliY","text_ar":"مَقْتَلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that they might publish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make known, my slaughter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asar~a A_ilayohi HadiyvFA","text_ar":"اَسَرَّ اـِلَيْهِ حَدِيثًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He revealed unto him a story"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secretly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) An ex. occurs in the Kur lxvi. 3. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asorarotu A_ilayohi Almawad~apa","text_ar":"اَسْرَرْتُ اـِلَيْهِ المَوَدَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmawad~api","text_ar":"بِالمَوَدَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I showed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manifested, to him love, or affection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) It is said in the Kur [lx. 1],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tusir~uwna A_ilayohimo biA@lomawad~api","text_ar":"تُسِرُّونَ اـِلَيْهِمْ بِا@لْمَوَدَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye reveal to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"the news of the Prophet"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is between you and them; the objective complement of the verb being suppressed: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almwd~p","text_ar":"المودّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be an objective complement, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a redundant corroborative, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a AlxiTaAma","text_ar":"اَخَذَ الخِطَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a bihi","text_ar":"اَخَذَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and this interpretation is correct; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isoraArN","text_ar":"اـِسْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a person necessarily implies revealing a secret to him and at the same time concealing it from another. (B.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^asar~uwhu biDaAEapF","text_ar":"وَاَسَرُّوهُ بِضَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xii. 19, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they concealed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept secret, his case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"making him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as an article of merchandise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they conjectured in their minds that they should obtain, by selling him, merchandise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotagaY","text_ar":"اِرْتَغَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rgw","text_ar":"رغو"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asr~ AlfaAtiHapa","text_ar":"اسرّ الفَاتِحَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlfaAtiHapi","text_ar":"بِالفَاتِحَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recited the Fátihah"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or First Chapter of the Kur-án]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secretly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inaudibly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the latter form of expression is a mistake. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asorarotuhu","text_ar":"اَسْرَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabotuhu A_ilaY Als~ir~i","text_ar":"نَسَبْتُهُ اـِلَى السِّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may mean either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I attributed it to secrecy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, like many phrases of this kind, by inversion,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I attributed to him secrecy, or mystery"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}